<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 17 日星期三 21:35:21 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistani Gov Promises ‘No Arrests’ at Khan’s Residence Before 24-Hour Surrender Deadline]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110426887" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/1d/1100128196_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_7f3476d7aa5cbe80135534142e010810.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1100128179" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html?share-img=1100128179"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Rahmat Gul</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">文件 - 巴基斯坦前总理伊姆兰汗于 2022 年 4 月 23 日在伊斯兰堡举行的新闻发布会上发表讲话。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="FILE - Former Pakistan's Prime Minister Imran Khan speaks during a news conference in Islamabad on April 23, 2022.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="文件 - 巴基斯坦前总理伊姆兰汗于 2022 年 4 月 23 日在伊斯兰堡举行的新闻发布会上发表讲话。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/1d/1100128196_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_dd456da6a0b72e5f0b140b11ff3aabbe.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/1d/1100128196_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_46e6bcb4e07735f3bd1fb063ed74a9e1.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/1d/1100128196_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_5edb1ae80681731b96e8763e9589df3a.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/08/1d/1100128196_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_dd456da6a0b72e5f0b140b11ff3aabbe.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Rahmat Gul </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">旁遮普邦政府发言人周三反驳了巴基斯坦前总理伊姆兰·汗的说法，告诉记者周四下午之前不会在汗的拉合尔豪宅“逮捕任何人”。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">旁遮普看守信息部长阿米尔米尔在接受巴基斯坦媒体采访时表示，汗的政党巴基斯坦正义运动党 (PTI) 的领导层必须在周四下午 2 点之前交出“30 至 40 名恐怖分子”，指的是据称参与的党员在最近几天对军事基地的袭击中。政府于周三下午发布了 24 小时的投降期限。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">米尔还拒绝了“伊姆兰汗声称已决定逮捕他”，指的是被罢免的政府首脑在社交媒体上的说法。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “可能是我下次被捕前的最后一条推文，”汗周三发推文说。 “警察已经包围了我的房子。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426887" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html?share-block=1110426890" data-title="“Probably my last tweet before my next arrest,” Khan tweeted on Wednesday. “Police has surrounded my house.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">媒体报道证实，旁遮普警方已经封锁了可汗在旁遮普省首府和巴基斯坦第二大城市拉合尔扎曼公园附近的豪宅周围的街道。结果，PTI 支持者开始在外面集会。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">米尔告诉媒体，安全机构证实，在扎曼公园地区，有“30 至 40 名恐怖分子袭击了包括真纳之家在内的陆军设施”，他们使用地理围栏或手机位置追踪。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “PTI 开始表现得像一个非国家行为体，”Mir 说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426887" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html?share-block=1110426894" data-title="&quot;PTI is starting to behave like a non-state actor,&quot; Mir stated."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些事件发生在可汗上周被捕之后，当时他还因 3 月份警方与其支持者之间的冲突而被指控犯有恐怖主义罪。汗的支持者走上街头抗议，数百人被拘留，其中包括 PTI 的高级成员。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>伊斯兰堡高等法院办公室下令逮捕汗，但被该国最高法院推翻，最高法院下令释放他。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在汗获释当天，驻拉合尔的著名独立政治和国防分析师哈桑·阿斯卡里·里兹维 (Hasan Askari Rizvi) 博士<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230511/khans-opponents-block-elections-and-order-his-arrest-fearing-ex-pm-cant-be-voted-out-1110267173.html" target="_blank">告诉卫星通讯社</a></u>，人们高度期待汗将在 48 小时内再次被捕。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>里兹维说：“我认为现任政府与伊姆兰汗之间的对抗在过去 2 到 3 年一直在持续，现在当他们逮捕伊姆兰汗时，这种对抗已经达到顶峰。”“我们认为这种对抗将继续下去，因为政府似乎对选举不感兴趣，他们想让他远离政治领域，这样他就不会成为选举的威胁。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426887" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html?share-block=1110426899" data-title="&amp;quot;I think the confrontation between the present government and Imran Khan has been going on for the last 2-3 years, and this has peaked now when they arrested Imran Khan,” Rizvi said. “We think that this confrontation will go on because the government doesn&amp;#x27;t appear to be interested in elections and they want to move him aside from the political domain so that he does not become a threat in the elections.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">汗于 2018 年成为总理，但在投票后于 2022 年 4 月被议会罢免，此举<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220409/us-bluntly-rejects-pakistan-pms-allegations-of-foreign-interference-ahead-of-no-confidence-vote-1094606715.html" target="_blank">被广泛视为华盛顿精心策划的</a></u>举动，以报复汗拒绝谴责俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别军事行动并加入反俄阵线制裁制度。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位被罢免的官员后来在批评新政府后于 2022 年 8 月被指控犯有恐怖主义罪，同年 11 月他在一次暗杀中幸免于难，他在暗杀中被枪击伤。这些指控<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220919/islamabad-court-drops-terror-charges-against-pakistans-former-pm-imran-khan-1100956425.html" target="_blank">后来被撤销</a></u>。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 21:11:19 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/pakistani-gov-promises-no-arrests-at-khans-residence-before-24-hour-surrender-deadline-1110426887.html<category>世界</category><category>伊姆兰汗</category><category>巴基斯坦</category><category>拉合尔</category><category>正义运动 (PTI)</category><category>逮捕</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Quad Leaders to Meet at G7 After Biden Nixes Summit to Handle Debt Ceiling Talks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110426242" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/18/1095733879_0:0:598:338_1440x900_80_0_1_8386768e181894f5dd2f93cdc81457c9.jpg?source-sid=not_sputnik_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1095733875" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html?share-img=1095733875"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© 照片 :</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">东京 ANI 四方领导人峰会</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Quad Leaders’ Summit in Tokyo


 


 - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="四方领导人东京峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/18/1095733879_0:0:599:336_1920x0_80_0_0_7af34f1beb1462a7998a4401cfdbc48f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/18/1095733879_0:0:599:336_640x0_80_0_0_fb107f23bb95fe9254d38854aad8f75a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/18/1095733879_0:0:599:336_1280x0_80_0_0_c4cc3203496d76ff60a61c512681e9c0.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e6/05/18/1095733879_0:0:599:336_1920x0_80_0_0_7af34f1beb1462a7998a4401cfdbc48f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 照片 : ANI </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">Quad 不是一个正式的联盟，但被广泛理解为试图协调华盛顿称之为“印度太平洋”地区的共同反华政策。这四个国家近年来都大幅增加了军费开支，称这是对中国构成的“威胁”的回应。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国总统拜登取消了他下周计划的大部分亚洲之行，包括访问巴布亚新几内亚和澳大利亚。悉尼将举办四方安全对话 (Quad) 领导人会议，其中包括拜登和印度总理纳伦德拉·莫迪、日本首相岸田文雄，并接待澳大利亚总理安东尼·艾博年。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">相反，四人将于本周晚些时候在日本广岛举行的<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/g7-summit-kicks-off-in-hiroshima-japan-1110421292.html" target="_blank">七国集团峰会</a></u>上发表讲话，拜登随后将返回美国，专注于<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-debt-ceiling-standoff-just-a-game-of-chicken-with-deal-at-11th-hour-1110417897.html">高风险的预算谈判，</a></u>而不是开始亚洲之行。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “Quad 是一个重要的机构，我们希望确保它发生在领导层，我们将在周末进行讨论，”Albanese 在一份关于反华集团的声明中说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426242" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html?share-block=1110426245" data-title="“The Quad is an important body and we want to make sure that it occurs at leadership level and we’ll be having that discussion over the weekend,” Albanese said in a statement about the anti-China bloc."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>政治风险分析师罗斯·法因戈尔德 (Ross Feingold) 拥有超过 20 年为客户提供台湾政治风险建议的经验</strong>，他周三对人造卫星表示，取消对四方关系的影响只是一个小小的减速带，四方关系将保持强劲，因为华盛顿必须保持重要地位在西太平洋的存在。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “太平洋岛国（PIC）领导人和东道主巴布亚新几内亚肯定会对拜登取消这部分行程感到失望，”范戈尔德说。 “近年来，中美在太平洋岛国争夺影响力的竞争备受关注，而且激烈且持续不断。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426242" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html?share-block=1110426249" data-title="“The Pacific Islands Countries (PIC) leaders, and the host Papua New Guinea, will certainly be disappointed that Biden canceled this part of the trip,” Feingold said. “Competition between China and the United States for influence in the Pacific Islands Countries has received significant attention in recent years and is intense and ongoing.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “2022 年 6 月 24 日，澳大利亚、日本、新西兰、英国和美国宣布建立蓝色太平洋伙伴关系，2022 年 7 月 12 日副总统卡马拉·哈里斯宣布美国与太平洋岛屿建立伙伴关系。随后于 2022 年 9 月 28 日至 29 日在白宫举行了首届美国-太平洋岛屿峰会，会上宣布了“21 世纪美国-太平洋岛屿伙伴关系路线图”和“首个太平洋伙伴关系战略” ，”他指出。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “中国在该地区同样高调的努力 [have] 包括 2022 年 5 月时任外交部长王毅访问所罗门群岛、基里巴斯、萨摩亚、斐济、汤加、瓦努阿图、巴布亚新几内亚和东帝汶；对密克罗尼西亚联邦的虚拟访问；以及在斐济举行的中国-太平洋岛国外长会议，此次访问宣布了气候变化、扶贫开发、防灾减灾和农业推广等方面的倡议，”范戈尔德说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426242" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html?share-block=1110426251" data-title="“China’s equally-high-profile efforts in the region [have] included in May 2022 then-Foreign Minister Wang Yi’s visits to Solomon Islands, Kiribati, Samoa, Fiji, Tonga, Vanuatu, Papua New Guinea and Timor-Leste; a virtual visit to the Federated States of Micronesia; and the China-Pacific Island Countries Foreign Ministers’ Meeting in Fiji, a trip that resulted in the announcement of initiatives in climate change, poverty alleviation and development, disaster prevention, and agricultural promotion,” Feingold said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “最终，美国在太平洋岛国的影响力将取决于援助和存在，”他说。 “在所罗门群岛重新开放大使馆和在汤加建立新的美国大使馆，这会有所帮助。美国海岸警卫队的存在普遍受到欢迎，特别是在它有助于执法行动打击非法、未报告和不受管制的捕鱼方面。存在还包括美国高级领导人的频繁访问，这将需要拜登总统弥补取消的对巴布亚新几内亚的访问。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登返回华盛顿的预算谈判重点是在联邦政府违约之前通过立法<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/mccarthy-deal-on-us-debt-ceiling-possible-but-talks-still-very-far-apart-1110407013.html" target="_blank">提高债务上限</a>， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230512/us-facing-significant-risk-of-default-in-first-two-weeks-of-june-1110303989.html" target="_blank">美国财政部警告说</a>，这可能会在“几天或几周内”发生。美国众议院的共和党多数派试图利用违约威胁迫使民主党同意大幅削减预算，否则他们会拒绝，例如削减社会计划。如果他们失败，政府违约，将破坏该国的信用评级并使其陷入经济危机。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">法因戈尔德表示，预计不会发生违约，但如果发生违约，其他与美国结盟的金融中心比北京更有可能受益。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “截至目前，华盛顿特区和金融界的利益相关者仍对不会发生违约持谨慎乐观态度。如果美国出现违约的可能性很小，亚洲的金融市场和政府可能会重新评估他们与美国的关系，无论是持有美国政府证券还是参与美国金融市场，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110426242" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html?share-block=1110426256" data-title="“As of now, stakeholders in Washington, DC, and the financial world remain cautiously optimistic that a default will not occur. On the outside chance that there is a US default, financial markets and governments in Asia will probably reassess their relationships with the United States, whether that’s holdings of US government securities or other participation in US financial markets,” he said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “虽然许多人认为这可能意味着中国的机会，但亚洲其他地区更有可能发挥避险作用，例如日本或新加坡。”</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 20:42:47 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/quad-leaders-to-meet-at-g7-after-biden-nixes-summit-to-handle-debt-ceiling-talks-1110426242.html<category>世界</category><category>G7</category><category>安东尼艾博年</category><category>纳伦德拉·莫迪</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>岸田文雄</category><category>四方安全对话 (QUAD) </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bring Back New York's Transit Police]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110425407" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110425717_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_b743e15dd43f990aed726324c553e947.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110425699" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/bring-back-new-yorks-transit-police-1110425407.html?share-img=1110425699"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Mary Altaffer</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2022 年 5 月 24 日，星期二，在纽约，当火车进入运河街 Q 和 N 站时，纽约交通局反恐小组的一名警察向火车做手势。安德鲁·阿卜杜拉 (Andrew Abdullah) 是一名在纽约市地铁列车上发生明显无端致命枪击事件的男子，他于周二被警方拘留，几小时前当局在社交媒体上发布了他的名字和照片，并恳请公众帮助找到他。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="A New York Police Officers with the Transit Bureau Anti Terrorism Unit gestures to the train conducted as a train enters the Canal St. Q and N station, Tuesday, May 24, 2022, in New York. Andrew Abdullah, the man wanted in an apparently unprovoked fatal shooting aboard a New York City subway train was taken into custody by police on Tuesday, hours after authorities posted his name and photo on social media and implored the public to help find him. - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="2022 年 5 月 24 日，星期二，在纽约，当火车进入运河街 Q 和 N 站时，纽约交通局反恐小组的一名警察向火车做手势。安德鲁·阿卜杜拉 (Andrew Abdullah) 是一名在纽约市地铁列车上发生明显无端致命枪击事件的男子，他于周二被警方拘留，几小时前当局在社交媒体上发布了他的名字和照片，并恳请公众帮助找到他。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110425717_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_1e2a622a47dbd41fb8b1e3f13b9051dd.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110425717_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_a92030876bf17b9ec87681c14c4a016e.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110425717_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_710d0f39817f9830f26852d5ee5a2595.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/11/1110425717_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_1e2a622a47dbd41fb8b1e3f13b9051dd.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Mary Altaffer </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="Ted Rall  - Sputnik International" title="泰德拉尔" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/02/13/1082125340_0:0:360:360_100x100_80_0_0_1ed1a3494a53cde87e19521c3658fe92.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">泰德拉尔</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_rall_ted/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">到访英国巴斯的游客了解到，该镇同名的公元 1 世纪温泉浴场在 5 世纪罗马政权垮台后遭到破坏。由于无人维护，水库淤塞并堵塞了排水系统，将设施和周围的建筑物掩埋在泥浆之下。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在罗马人的训练下，当地的英国人最初知道如何在他们的帝国主人回到意大利后让浴室保持运转。习惯改变了；英国人不像罗马人那样经常洗澡。时间流逝，知识褪色。最终，即使当地人产生了对热水灌篮的渴望，也没有人能够让系统再次运行。基本上，英国人忘记了他们所知道的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">纽约市衰落的地铁系统中最新的头条新闻暴力事件，乔丹·尼利 (Jordan Neely) 窒息死亡，他是一名 30 岁的无家可归的精神分裂症患者，死于 24 岁的前海军陆战队员丹尼尔·彭尼 (Daniel Penny) 之手，这让我和其他年长的人纽约人渴望纽约市交通警察。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">就像巴斯的居民一样，纽约忘记了交通警察。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">从 1953 年到 1995 年，美国最大的公共交通系统拥有自己的警察局，独立于纽约警察局 (NYPD)。到 1994 年，该部队雇用了 4,500 名军装和文职人员，成为美国所有部门中第六大部门。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p> 1974 年版的“夺取佩勒姆 1-2-3”展示了运输警察的技能，他们接受了如何切断三轨电源、营救被困在车站之间的乘客以及追捕嫌疑人到隧道、废弃车站的技能和地下紧急出口。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">我们不知道在 Penny 让 Neely 窒息 15 分钟以结束他的生命之前究竟发生了什么。然而，作为一个坐了40多年地铁的纽约人，我可以证明，纽约人在地铁上遇到意外时，是得不到任何帮助的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">你被困在街道下方一百英尺的一个狭窄的金属盒子里。大多数线路上下一辆车的门都锁着，包括尼利和佩妮乘坐的那辆车。纽约地铁车厢里没有电话亭。手机不能在车站之间使用。没有监控摄像头。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">而且没有警察。从来没有任何警察。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">并非总是如此。地铁上一次如此危险和诡异是在 1980 年代：现在有更多精神分裂症无家可归者，那时候抢劫案更多。总的来说，效果是一样的：令人不安和焦虑。但交通警察减轻了乘客的恐惧。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <a href="https://nypost.com/2016/03/02/nypd-putting-a-cop-on-every-subway-to-combat-slashings/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">每列火车都有一两名过境警察巡逻</a>。他们是一个熟悉的景象，当他们从一辆车跳到另一辆车时，他们转动警棍。我永远不会忘记一个裸体男人坐在我旁边的时间；一名过境警察差点从我们身边走过，然后又看了一眼。 <strong>“哟，”警官边说边用警棍敲打着裸露的裸体先生的膝盖。 “忘记了什么？”</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">交通警察部署了大量卧底警察。一天晚上，我坐在一位推着婴儿车的年轻孕妇对面。警察无线电的噼啪声从她衣服下面的某个地方发出。拿出了她的徽章和枪，她扔下了她的假婴儿奶和婴儿车（婴儿也是一个洋娃娃），然后她去寻找荣耀和公共安全。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">我不太喜欢警察，但我怎么能不被打动呢？</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">以冗余和低效为由——纽约警察局和交通警察使用不同的无线电系统——时任市长鲁迪朱利安尼废除了交通警察并将其并入纽约警察局。 （他的真正动机是巩固他的政治权力。）一个新的纽约警察局运输局应该取代他们；<strong>在现实生活中，警察的存在从地铁系统中消失了。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">我们需要更多细节，但在撰写本文时，我同意地方检察官对佩妮提出二级过失杀人罪指控的决定。 Neely 没有碰任何人，包括 Penny。佩妮所要做的就是等一分钟，也许三分钟，等下一站的车门打开，然后让尼利听他大喊大叫。<strong>限制/窒息他 15 分钟是不合理的。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">与此同时，在这样一种情况下，悲剧是不可避免的：通勤者得不到保护，只能靠自己对地铁车厢的判断，而地铁车厢往往充当滚动的无家可归者收容所和疯人院，我们的政治阶层已决定不这样做。值得照顾。尼利是受害者。纽约人也应该以 2.75 美元的票价享受从 A 地到 B 地的安全、可靠的旅行。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为了让人们感到安全，纽约市市长埃里克·亚当斯 (Eric Adams) 让地铁售票员在每一站<a href="https://www.thecity.nyc/2022/11/15/23451820/new-subway-police-presence-conductors-safety" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">宣布</a>：“如果你有任何问题、疑虑、报告，纽约警察局就在这个车站。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>真是笑话。地铁的麻烦是很快的麻烦——而且它通常发生在火车上，而不是车站，就像在 Neely-Penny 对抗中看到的那样。此外，车站很大，至少有两个完整的城市街区长，有多个入口。找警察就像大海捞针。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">城市地铁系统中总会存在犯罪和其他问题。但是纽约可以通过恢复旧的交通警察来让乘客感到更安全，让他们的警察以 24-7 的速度在每列火车上巡逻。例如，佩尼如果知道他的 F 列火车将驶入百老汇-拉斐特站并在一分钟后被一名警察登上，他可能不会一直掐住尼利的脖子。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">我们必须忘掉。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <em>（泰德·拉尔（Ted Rall，推特：@tedrall），政治漫画家、专栏作家和图画小说家，与漫画家斯科特·斯坦蒂斯共同主持左派与右派<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/id/podcast/dmz-america-with-ted-rall-scott-stantis/id1580768498" target="_blank">DMZ America 播</a>客。您可以支持泰德的强硬政治漫画和专栏，看看他的工作首先是赞助他在<a href="http://www.patreon.com/tedrall" target="_blank">Patreon</a>上的工作。）</em></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 19:45:07 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/bring-back-new-yorks-transit-police-1110425407.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/bring-back-new-yorks-transit-police-1110425407.html<category>分析</category><category>纽约警察局 (NYPD)</category><category>纽约市</category><category>鲁迪朱利安尼</category><category>我们</category><category>锁喉</category><category>死亡威胁</category><category>地铁站</category><category>地铁袭击</category><category>地铁列车</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[US Drug Shortage Nears Record High Amid Supply Chain Disruptions - Reports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110425572" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107843/74/1078437449_0:0:640:427_1440x900_80_0_1_35239cdef83c3e2a8b930092dae57421.jpg?source-sid=cc_by-sa_20" data-photoview-image-id="1078437447" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/us-drug-shortage-nears-record-high-amid-supply-chain-disruptions---reports-1110425572.html?share-img=1078437447"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="CC BY-SA 2.0">CC BY-SA 2.0</a> / <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/fillmorephotography/" title="迈克尔陈/Flickr">Michael Chen/Flickr</a> /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">药片</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_by-sa_20" alt="Pills - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="药丸" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107843/74/1078437449_0:52:641:412_1920x0_80_0_0_2bc21751c1b7b53a9f01b11e8d4950c3.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107843/74/1078437449_0:52:641:412_640x0_80_0_0_136d3046c8e76e344cfb9ebe7cf2ccfc.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107843/74/1078437449_0:52:641:412_1280x0_80_0_0_c329ef1bbd01ae48d3c8409f1e04e44f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107843/74/1078437449_0:52:641:412_1920x0_80_0_0_2bc21751c1b7b53a9f01b11e8d4950c3.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" title="CC BY-SA 2.0">CC BY-SA 2.0</a> / <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/fillmorephotography/" title="迈克尔陈/Flickr">Michael Chen/Flickr</a> / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国媒体周三报道，由于供应链问题和制造停工，美国正面临创纪录的抗癌药物短缺和其他危及生命的疾病。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，抗癌药物是数百种短缺药物之一，其中还包括心脏搭桥手术药物、抗生素和儿童泰诺。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告补充说，治疗肺癌、乳腺癌、膀胱癌和卵巢癌的通用化疗形式也加剧了人们的担忧。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，鉴于面临短缺的化疗药物数量，约翰霍普金斯医学院教授阿曼达费德称这种情况为“公共卫生紧急情况”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报告称，白宫和国会正在关注摇摇欲坠的仿制药市场，该市场约占国内处方药的 90%。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">报道补充说，拜登政府还组建了一个团队，以减少药品供应链对来自印度和中国的药品和药物成分的严重依赖。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 19:21:18 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-drug-shortage-nears-record-high-amid-supply-chain-disruptions---reports-1110425572.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/us-drug-shortage-nears-record-high-amid-supply-chain-disruptions---reports-1110425572.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>药品</category><category>处方药</category><category>药物运输</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[G7 Summit Kicks Off in Hiroshima, Japan]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">七国集团领导人将于 5 月 19 日至 21 日在日本举行会议，讨论当前的地缘政治和经济挑战——即在乌克兰危机和对俄罗斯制裁的情况下北约的扩张。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">今年的 G7 会议点具有黑暗的象征意义——1945 年 8 月，美国用核武器轰炸了广岛，立即造成数十万人死亡，并将这座曾经繁荣的城市变成了一座放射性墓地。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国是唯一一个在战斗中使用过核武器的国家，历史学家一致认为，这一举动对苏联来说更像是一场奇观，而不是战术上必要的一步。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，日本收起骄傲，拥抱西方价值观，成为美国的亲密盟友，随波逐流。现在世界上最大的墓地之一将举办一次关于北约东扩的峰会。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="infographics"><div class="article__infographics-media  m-border" data-uid="1110421293"><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="desktop"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420422.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="mobile"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420422.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="infographics"><div class="article__infographics-media  m-border" data-uid="1110421296"><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="desktop"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420596.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="mobile"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420596.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="infographics"><div class="article__infographics-media  m-border" data-uid="1110421299"><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="desktop"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420770.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="mobile"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420770.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="infographics"><div class="article__infographics-media  m-border" data-uid="1110421902"><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="desktop"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420947.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="mobile"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110420947.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="infographics"><div class="article__infographics-media  m-border" data-uid="1110421905"><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="desktop"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110421121.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__infographics_variant" data-type="mobile"><img media-type="hires" data-source-sid="sputnik_infographics" alt="G7 Summit in Hiroshima - Sputnik International" title="G7广岛峰会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/images/07e7/05/11/1110421121.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 19:15:54 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/g7-summit-kicks-off-in-hiroshima-japan-1110421292.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/g7-summit-kicks-off-in-hiroshima-japan-1110421292.html<category>多媒体</category><category>资料图</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kinzhal Missile Strike Destroyed Five Patriot Launchers in Kiev - Russia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110424974" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107919/12/1079191229_0:0:2656:1659_1440x900_80_0_1_afbd596ff3b23cf9df56a79d07dc2631.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1079191227" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/kinzhal-missile-strike-destroyed-five-patriot-launchers-in-kiev---russia-1110424974.html?share-img=1079191227"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Алексей Майшев</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">装备 Kinzhal 的 MiG-31 在飞越克里姆林宫期间重复即将到来的胜利大阅兵，2020 年 5 月 4 日。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Kinzhal-armed MiG-31s during their flight past the Kremlin amid the repetition for the upcoming Victory Parade, May 4, 2020. - Sputnik International, 1920, 17.05.2023" title="2020 年 5 月 4 日，Kinzhal 武装的 MiG-31 在飞越克里姆林宫期间重复举行胜利大阅兵。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107919/12/1079191229_0:0:2656:1495_1920x0_80_0_0_1272e2f0dd5fe6480298c714834798a5.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107919/12/1079191229_0:0:2656:1495_640x0_80_0_0_152e7e056668a9a88a3cddac7d48c2e5.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107919/12/1079191229_0:0:2656:1495_1280x0_80_0_0_88c13eec1cb6a773644cb740301af4de.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107919/12/1079191229_0:0:2656:1495_1920x0_80_0_0_1272e2f0dd5fe6480298c714834798a5.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Алексей Майшев</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：虽然基辅声称已经拦截了六枚 Kinzhals，但俄罗斯国防部长谢尔盖绍伊古在接受人造卫星采访时告诉人造卫星，乌克兰的报道在各个方面都是错误的，并指出只有几枚俄罗斯导弹足以穿透基辅的防御系统。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “根据经核实的信息，由于<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/unstoppable-kinzhal-one-us-made-patriot-cracked-up-more-to-come-1110424287.html" target="_blank">Kinzhal 高超音速导弹系统对基辅市的一次袭击</a>，一个多功能雷达站以及美国制造的爱国者防空导弹系统的五个发射器被击中并完全2023 年 5 月 16 日被摧毁，”俄罗斯国防部说。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110424974" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/kinzhal-missile-strike-destroyed-five-patriot-launchers-in-kiev---russia-1110424974.html?share-block=1110424975" data-title="&amp;quot;According to verified information, as a result of a strike by the Kinzhal hypersonic missile system in the city of Kiev a multifunctional radar station, as well as five launchers of the Patriot anti-aircraft missile system manufactured by the United States were hit and completely destroyed on May 16, 2023,&amp;quot; the Russian Defense Ministry said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Kinzhal（直译“匕首”）是俄罗斯总统弗拉基米尔·普京于 2018 年 3 月公布的新型战略武器之一。它于 2017 年 12 月首次进入战斗值班，进行了广泛的飞行和战斗测试。这种具有核武器能力的武器是任何国家部署的第一种高超音速导弹系统。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Kinzhal 的射程超过 2,000 公里（1,200 英里）。它能够达到高达 10 马赫（12,250 公里/小时或 7,612 英里/小时）的速度，同时还能执行规避机动，这有助于 Kinzhal 几乎不受敌方空中导弹防御系统的伤害。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 17 May 2023 19:01:31 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/kinzhal-missile-strike-destroyed-five-patriot-launchers-in-kiev---russia-1110424974.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230517/kinzhal-missile-strike-destroyed-five-patriot-launchers-in-kiev---russia-1110424974.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>Kinzhal 导弹系统</category><category>俄罗斯国防部</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>乌克兰危机</category></item></channel></rss>